 ice-rink, which was always unlucky: last winter it had been thaw after thaw and a pool in place of ice, and now such a cold spell that not even schoolboys were up to skating. In the parks little, high-breasted birds lay on the snow with feet in the air. The helpless mercury under the influence of its surroundings, fell ever lower and lower. And even the polar bears in the zoo found that the management had overdone it.

